
[1]devastation

   DEVASTATION, n. [L.]

   1. Waste; ravage; desolation; destruction of works of art and natural
   productions which are necessary or useful to man; havock; as by armies,
   fire, flood, &c.

   2. IN law, waste of the goods of the deceased by an executor, or
   administrator.
